Sentencas: Three-dimensional microstructure of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF6428), is obtained by a dual-beam focused ion beam-scanning electron microscope, and its overpotential is predicted by the lattice Boltzmann method.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: Gaseous, ionic and electronic transport equations coupled with electrochemical reaction at the gas/solid interface in the three-dimensional microstructure are solved with an assumption of local equilibrium in the solid oxide.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: The gas transport is modeled by the dusty gas model.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: The numerical simulation is conducted under the current density conditions of 0.01, 0.05, 0.1 and 0.2 A/cm(2).
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: Predicted cathode overpotentials agreed well with the experimental results.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: However, predicted overpotential was very large at O-2 = 20%, T = 973 K and i = 0.2 A/cm(2) case due to the decline of ionic conductivity at low oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: Three-dimensional chemical potential and current vector distributions inside LSCF microstructure are presented.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: Ionic and electronic current stream lines are uniform and smooth, which indicates good ionic and electronic conductions as well as wide electrochemically active areas inside the LSCF microstructure.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope

Sentencas: Present method will be an effective tool for investigating local oxygen potential field which affects local reactions, diffusions and physical properties of the MIEC cathodes.
Titulo: Three-dimensional numerical analysis of mixed ionic and electronic conducting cathode reconstructed by focused ion beam scanning electron microscope
